Ship location and the conditions where the ship was located are maintained on this site for one year.   The NOAA fleet ranges from large oceanographic research vessels capable of exploring the world's deepest ocean, to smaller ships responsible for charting the shallow bays and inlets of the United States. The fleet supports a wide range of marine activities including fisheries research, nautical charting, and ocean and climate studies.</dct:description>         <dcat:keyword>{oceans</dcat:keyword>
